# Architecture Guardrails Rule

When editing the project, follow the approved architecture and do not bypass intended boundaries between UI, API, domain services, and data access.

- UI/pages must not contain privileged business logic or direct database writes.
- Backend routers should delegate to service/domain layer before data-access layer.
- Reusable async/query logic should be encapsulated and testable.
- Keep screens/pages focused on composition, navigation, and view state rendering.
- Every user-facing screen must support loading, empty/not-found, error, and success states when relevant.
- Never place secrets in frontend code.
- If a use case needs privileged actions, enforce in backend with role checks and audit logging.
